      {
        "id": 2219409,
        "name": null,
        "username": "GregT",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/gregt/{size}/625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-14T17:37:03.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>In case you don\u2019t want to read an entire Asimov article, they\u2019re usually some version of the same thing, so here\u2019s a handy summary.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Hey! Try wine from this grape or region!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Unfortunately, some producers used new oak! They\u2019re ruining everything!</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Thank god some producers do things the traditional way, whatever that was.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Those last producers are the best. They make food-friendly wines.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The pendulum is swinging back to the traditional producers.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The end.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
