      {
        "id": 2219719,
        "name": "Ian Sutton",
        "username": "Ian_Sutton",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/ian_sutton/{size}/2266_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-07-14T23:20:41.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Interestingly when I bought a bottle of Pepe Md\u2019A in Ivrea, the lady in the shop made a point of recommending a proper decanting of the the wine. She said it did tend to have significant bottle-stink from the (natural) winemaking that benefitted from aeration. Not steering me away, but trying to ensure I didn\u2019t get a nasty surprise, and handled quite diplomatically.</p>",
